    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-02-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="71" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d71">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1257.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-02-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 1, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>. I have received a despatch of the 3d
                            ultimo from Mr. Robinson, our consul at Port Mahon, in which it is
                            stated that on the 1st of that month, which <pb facs="0151" n="111" xml:id="pg_111"/> was a Spanish “fiesta,” the ships in the harbor,
                            as usual, displayed their national flags and signals, but that the
                            master of the Linda Florida, Captain Daniel Hallowell, seized the
                            occasion to insult the United States by hoisting upon his vessel, which
                            was British registered and manned, in addition to the flags and signals
                            of England, the flags of the insurgents against the United States. I
                            will thank you to call the attention of her Majesty’s government to this
                            insult.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>. Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
